article.headline: Portland St. 78, Rice 74
article.story: HOUSTON -- Jeremiah Dominguez scored 24 points, leading Portland State to a come-from-behind 78-74 win over Rice on Saturday. Rice led 36-33 at halftime, but was outscored 45-38 in the second half. Dominguez was 7 of 12 from the field, including four 3-pointers. Dominic Waters added 18 points for the Vikings (1-0), while Jamie Jones scored 13 points and grabbed 13 rebounds. Dominguez hit a key 3-pointer to give the Vikings a 76-70 lead with a minute to play. Waters hit two free throws in the final 26 seconds to help seal the win. Cory Pflieger scored 17 points to lead Rice (0-1). Aleks Perka scored 15 points, and Trey Stanton had 14 for the Owls, who were playing in the newly renovated Tudor Fieldhouse.
